Study by Lancashire's Edge Hill University found link between anxiety and grades achieved in GCSE exams . 
  Pupils who worry are more likely to do badly than those who are less anxious . 
  Principal at Burlington Danes Academy Michael Ribton offers advice . 
  He says parents should draw up a revision timetable and set goals . 
  Parents should also engage with children to help them revise . 
  Study found pupils who worry about their exams do worse . 
 